Description: Fragment of strap handle of a probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine, micaceous, brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 37, 5. Name Simias. An example in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1601)
